items.name: Hand-Gesture-Classification
items.description: Hand Gesture Classification is a Python project that uses computer vision and machine learning to classify hand gestures in real-time. By leveraging the MediaPipe framework for hand landmark detection and TensorFlow for model training, this system captures live webcam video, detects hand poses, and predicts gesture categories.

items.name: Automated_Ad_Storyboard_Synthesis
items.description: The objective of this challenge is to develop a machine learning framework that automates the transformation of textual advertisement descriptions into visually compelling storyboards.

items.name: twingraph
items.description: TwinGraph is a Python framework for distributed container orchestration using Kubernetes clusters, Docker Compose/Swarm or cloud resources on AWS (AWS Lambda, AWS Batch, Amazon EKS). Applications include high-throughput simulations, simulation-driven optimization, Digital Twins and machine learning.

items.name: Stock-Market-Analysis-A-Two-Stage-Comparative-Stacking-Approach-using-Pyspark-Jan_2024
items.description: This project aims to enhance the accuracy and efficiency of stock market predictions by employing a sophisticated machine learning methodology. This project leverages the power of PySpark, a robust framework for distributed data processing, to handle large datasets and perform complex computations.

items.name: Indian-Restaurant-and-location-Prediction-
items.description: Welcome to Indian Restaurant Name and Location Prediction Project! This innovative project leverages machine learning techniques and is implemented using the Python Flask framework.

items.name: Building-Machine-Learning-Solutions-for-O-RAN-Use-Cases-in-5G-NR-Networks-INTERNSHIP-Aug_2023
items.description: This project focuses on developing machine learning solutions for various use cases within 5G New Radio (NR) networks, specifically under the Open Radio Access Network (O-RAN) framework.

items.description: A framework for easy application of established machine learning techniques on large, multi-dimensional images.
